name: Port strike update
summary: Following a period of disruption, dockworkers at ports along the US East and Gulf Coasts have suspended their strike after reaching a tentative agreement on wages with employers. The deal includes a 62% pay increase over six years, significantly higher than the "nearly 50% wage increase" initially proposed. This development averted a potential economic crisis by preventing a prolonged shutdown of ports, which would have impacted the supply chain and availability of various products. The strike suspension allows workers to return to their jobs immediately, bringing relief to industries and consumers who rely on these ports for essential goods. The resolution highlights the negotiating advantage held by dockworkers in this labor dispute.

name: Aurora forecast
summary: Multiple news sources are reporting an increased likelihood of Northern Lights sightings across the northern United States this weekend due to a geomagnetic storm. According to the Alaska's News Source, a geomagnetic storm watch is in effect, indicating increased activity in the Earth's magnetic field that can lead to enhanced displays of the aurora borealis. States such as Minnesota, Wisconsin, Michigan, and Maine are expected to have the best views, while visibility may also be possible in Kentucky, Indiana, and California. Experts from NOAA and Space.com note that the solar flares responsible for the aurora borealis can be unpredictable, so the actual visibility may vary. Additionally, some regions may experience reduced viewing chances due to cloudy weather conditions or bright moon phases.

name: Tom Selleck
summary: In an exclusive interview with TV Insider, Tom Selleck discusses the upcoming conclusion of "Blue Bloods," expressing his thoughts on the show's ending. In interviews with Deadline, Us Weekly, Fox News, New York Post, PEOPLE, E! News, The Independent, Geo News, and Just Jared, Selleck expresses his frustration with CBS's decision to cancel the long-running series. He believes that the show was "taken for granted" and that the decision was made without proper consideration. Selleck shares his regrets regarding his character, Frank, and reveals his thoughts on the final scene. He also hints at what may be in store for his future endeavors.

name: Tyre Nichols
summary: A jury in Memphis has convicted some of the former police officers involved in the fatal beating of Tyre Nichols on lesser charges. The three officers were acquitted of the most serious charge, second-degree murder. They were found guilty of various other charges, including second-degree aggravated assault, aggravated kidnapping, and official misconduct. The verdict comes after weeks of testimony and evidence presented in the trial. The jury is still deliberating on the charges against the remaining three former officers involved in Nichols' death.
